node.text: Твои кадры стали для меня источником вдохновения

Keep a camera in your hands—for the in-between moments, the frames that build the bigger picture.

When I head out to shoot, there’s always a camera on the passenger seat, and one in my hands when I’m walking to and from a spot—usually at golden hour. No second-guessing, no debating whether to take it out of the bag. If it’s already there, I won’t miss a shot.

Spending time doing street photography taught me that some of the best frames happen in between planned shots. It made me quicker, more observant, and more open to shooting beyond what I set out for. That mindset carried over into the outdoors—now I look for moments everywhere, not just when I reach the “spot.”

More often than not, these in-between frames end up being my favourites from a session. So here are a few recent ones.

How often do you shoot the “in-between” moments?

Enjoy your Sunday!

—Gar
